# /validate-all — Cross-Project Validation

## Purpose
3-level validation of all project modules, ensuring cross-project consistency.

## Level 1: Syntax (Lint)
Run lint on each module:
{{#each modules}}
- `{{name}}` ({{role}}): `cd {{directory}} && make lint`
{{/each}}

## Level 2: Functional (Tests)
Run unit tests on each module:
{{#each modules}}
- `{{name}}` ({{role}}): `cd {{directory}} && make test`
{{/each}}

## Level 3: Integration (Cross-Project Contracts)
{{#if (and (hasRole "frontend") (hasRole "backend"))}}
Verify consistency between frontends and backends:

### Types/DTOs
- Compare frontend types/interfaces with backend response models
- Verify required fields are present on both sides
{{#modulesOfRole "frontend"}}
- Frontend: `{{directory}}/src/types/`
{{/modulesOfRole}}
{{#modulesOfRole "backend"}}
- Backend: `{{directory}}/src/` (response models)
{{/modulesOfRole}}

### Endpoints
- Verify frontend API calls match existing backend routes
- Validate parameter compatibility (path, query, body)

### Environment Variables
- Verify all variables referenced in code exist in `.env.example`
{{else}}
Integration validation not applicable (single-role project).
{{/if}}

## Report
Generate consolidated report:
```
=== Cross-Project Validation ===
--- Level 1: Syntax ---
{{#each modules}}
  {{name}}: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
{{/each}}
--- Level 2: Functional ---
{{#each modules}}
  {{name}}: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
{{/each}}
--- Level 3: Integration ---
  Types: ✅ / ❌
  Endpoints: ✅ / ❌
  Env vars: ✅ / ❌
```
{{/if}}
